    "We particularly derived inspiration from the Scandinavian political Participatory Design tradition which prioritizes empowerment and the right to have a voice and a say in design (Iivari et al. 2022).",
    "We also relied on speculative and critical design traditions that invite critically probing, questioning and dreaming about (alternative) futures, using design as a form of critique or a political tool (Iivari et al. 2022).",
    "Such approaches enable both critique and action taking for a better world.",
    "They entail ethical consideration of right and wrong and foster empowerment -of individuals and collectives, in relational and motivational senses (Iivari et al. 2022).",
    "In the project, children designed diverse AI/ML systems with advanced surveillance, sensing, reasoning and adaptation abilities to tackle a wicked societal problem of bullying."
